{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048177,"nonce":"s4dELZ4UQrpJPrFb/lKxv4fqwDo=","title":"Web UI: Two-shelf layout collapse and resize not working correctly","message":"[Imported from GitHub #46] (created 2026-01-30T02:35:43Z)\n\n## Problem\n\nThe two-shelf layout in the web UI has several related issues:\n\n### 1. Top shelf cannot be collapsed\nOnly the bottom shelf can be collapsed. There's no working affordance to collapse the top shelf (model editor) to show only the bottom shelf (validation/training/analysis).\n\n### 2. Resize divider limited to 50% minimum for top shelf\nWhen dragging the divider between shelves, the top shelf cannot be made smaller than ~50% of the viewport height. The bottom shelf cannot grow larger than 50%.\n\n**Expected**: Full range of splits from top-collapsed to bottom-collapsed, with only a small minimum height (e.g., 44px collapsed header) for either shelf.\n\n### 3. Canvas scaling asymmetry\n- Shrinking bottom shelf (expanding top) → canvas area grows, but graph doesn't scale up\n- Expanding bottom shelf (shrinking top) → graph scales down\n\nThis causes the graph to get progressively smaller with repeated resize operations.\n\n## Context\n\nThe two-shelf layout was implemented in commit `44ab6bf`. Refinements were attempted in `ce3c1ac` (adjust heights, initialization logic), but the core issues persist.\n\n## What was tried\n\n- Adjusted `MIN_BOTTOM_HEIGHT`, `MAX_BOTTOM_HEIGHT`, `DEFAULT_BOTTOM_HEIGHT` in `layoutStore.ts`\n- Added initialization logic for bottom shelf height\n- Header has chevron buttons for shelf toggles\n\n## Files involved\n\n- `web/src/stores/layoutStore.ts` - shelf state and constraints\n- `web/src/components/layout/Header.tsx` - toggle buttons\n- `web/src/components/layout/TopShelf.tsx`\n- `web/src/components/layout/BottomShelf.tsx`\n- `web/src/App.tsx` - layout container and resize logic\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n1. Both shelves independently collapsible (with NAND constraint: at least one open)\n2. Divider allows full range of splits\n3. Graph maintains relative size when shelf proportions change (bidirectional)\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}